<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1930,2034]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,152,364]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,1930,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[286,512,1931,1956]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leuciscus">
<emphasis box="[286,512,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="17">Equulites leuciscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other leiognathids by the following combination of features: a rhomboid shaped body (&gt; 
<number box="[633,663,1968,1994]" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" value="38.0">38</number>
% BD); a dorsal flank pattern of dark, thin to broad semicircular and oval shapes, a markedly elongate 
<number box="[600,615,2008,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
nd dorsal fin spine, a translucent triangular lateral flank patch in males that does not reach the pectoral-fin base or comprise a continuous or broken midlateral stripe. 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leuciscus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">Equulites leuciscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[671,818,189,214]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis box="[671,818,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">E. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[877,1016,189,214]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rivulatus">
<emphasis box="[877,1016,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">E. rivulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by possessing a much deeper body (
<number box="[159,230,226,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" value="42.5" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="38.0">38-47</number>
% vs. 
<number box="[303,416,226,252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" value="21.1" valueMax="29.7" valueMin="12.5">12.5-29.7</number>
% of SL) and from 
<taxonomicName box="[648,846,226,251]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laterofenestra">
<emphasis box="[648,846,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">E. laterofenestra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[904,1069,226,251]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="klunzingeri">
<emphasis box="[904,1069,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">E. klunzingeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a translucent flank patch in males that does not reach the pectoral fin axil. The triangular lateral flank patch of males in 
<taxonomicName box="[1221,1360,264,289]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leuciscus">
<emphasis box="[1221,1360,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">E. leuciscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
easily distinguishes it from 
<emphasis box="[410,741,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[410,548,301,326]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="antongil">E. antongil</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[561,741,301,326]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stercorarius">E. stercorarius</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis box="[810,1021,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[810,1016,301,326]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="moretoniensis">E. moretoniensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
all of which have a continuous or broken midlateral stripe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption box="[151,892,833,857]" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,892,833,857]" box="[151,892,833,857]" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">
